##------------------------------------------------------------------------
##  Useage                     
##------------------------------------------------------------------------

@NODE Useage "Programme Useage"
                             Programme Useage

After starting the programme by double-clicking on its icon the user
will see a window titled ScionBrowser displaying the family tree for 
the currently displayed person in Scion Genealogist will be displayed. 
This window will be opened on the first Scion Genealogist screen found. 

It is possible to have multiple instances of Scion Genealogist active at
a time (up to 10) each using a different database. They are distinguished 
by their screen names. The first instance is named SCIONGEN, up to 9 more 
will be named SCIONGEN1 ... SCIONGEN9. This is as well the search order
used by ScionBrowser.


At the bottom of the window there is a @{"panel" LINK Panel} shown.

Besides using the mouse, some functionality can be obtained using the 
keyboard keys. These are

@{bold "Arrow Up"} 
         Move the window upwards, the family tree display moves down
         
@{bold "Arrow Down"} 
         Move the window downwards, the family tree display moves up

@{bold "Arrow Left"}         
         Move the window left, the family tree display moves right
         
@{bold "Arrow Right"}
         Move the window right, the family tree display moves left
         
@{bold "Shift + Arrow Up"} 
@{bold "Shift + Arrow Down"} 
@{bold "Shift + Arrow Left"}         
@{bold "Shift + Arrow Right"}
         Similar behaviour as without Shift key, however instead of moving
         one pixel, the display jumps a magic amount of pixels.

@{bold "h"}
@{bold "Shift + h"}
         Brings the display back home. This is where the context person
         appears in the middle of the window.
         
@{bold "Help"}
         Starts Multiview to display the online help guide.
         
@ENDNODE

##------------------------------------------------------------------------
##  Panel                     
##------------------------------------------------------------------------

@NODE Panel "Panel"
                             Panel                    

The panel basically looks as follows:

+--------------------------------------------------------------------+
| Context  [IRN] [Name        ] [Birthdate]                          |
|                                                         [^]        |
|    Info  [IRN] [Name        ] [Birthdate]            [<][H][>]     |
|                                                         [v]        |
|    [Select]   [Quit]   [Info>Context]  [Update Scion]              |
+--------------------------------------------------------------------+

The bottom row consists of three buttons with the following functionality:

Select
      Will display a list view gadget with all available persons.
      
Quit
      Will end the programme. Same as closing the window using the window
      close gadget.
      
Info>Context
      Will use the person displayed as Info to become the Context person.
      This results in the family tree to be updated accordingly.
      
Update Scion

      Will update the Scion Genealogist personal data window to display
      the personal data of the current info person.
      
At the righthand side there are 5 cursor buttons. Clicking one of the
arrow buttons will scroll the family tree into the appropriate direction.
(Actually the window is moved into the appropriate direction whilst the
family tree remains still.)
The H button provides a mean to get the context person back @{bold "H"}ome
to the center of the window. This is needed because the current version
of ScionBrowser allows to scroll the tree off the window.

The rows Context and Info show the @{"IRN" LINK Definitions}, name and birthdate of the context
person and info person respectively.

@ENDNODE



##------------------------------------------------------------------------
##  Definitions
##------------------------------------------------------------------------

@NODE Definitions "Definitions"
                             Definitions

Context Person
      
      The actual family tree always displays only a part of the relations
      found in the database. This part is dependent on the Context Person.
      This is the person setting the context for the currently displayed
      family tree. To the left of the Context Person all ancestors are 
      drawn, to the right all dependents.
      
Info Person

      The family tree only displays the IRNs of persons. In order to
      identify a person, i.e. get Name, First name and Birthdate it
      is possible to single click on any IRN in the family tree. The
      before mentioned data for that IRN will be displayed as Info Person.
      
IRN

      The @{bold "I"}ndividual @{bold "R"}ecord @{bold "N"}umber is used by
      Scion Genealogist to uniqely identify each person in the database.
      

@ENDNODE

