##------------------------------------------------------------------------
##  ErrorMessage
##------------------------------------------------------------------------

@NODE ErrorMessage "Error Messages"
                             Error Messages
Attention#Attention#Attention#Attention#Attention#Attention#Attention

   The error display mechanism is currently under revision and likely
   to be changed. The following gives only an idea.
   
Attention#Attention#Attention#Attention#Attention#Attention#Attention

Currently ScionBrowser will produce error messages in a CLI type output
window. This window will remain active until it is manually closed by
the user.

The general format of each message is:

      ScionBrowser <ErrorType>: <Message>
      
      
ScionBrowser distinguishes 5 different error types or categories 
of messages:

      WARNING
         
            A warning is a information to the user which notifies about
            some unusual condition. However, ScionBrowser is capable to
            assume the correct condition and normal operations will 
            proceed with this assumption.
            
      ERROR
      
            An error is an information to the user about a critical
            condition. Because of the nature and therefore its 
            criticality, ScionBrowser is not able to resume normal
            operations and quits.
            
      DEBUG
      
            A message labeled DEBUG should not occur in an official
            release version of ScionBrowser. If it does please notify the
            @{"author" LINK "Problem"} about this message and provide
            as many details as possible under what condition this 
            message appeared.
                  
      INFORMATION
      
            An information is merely a message giving the user some 
            useful information.
            
      INTERNAL

            A message labeled INTERNAL notifies the user about some
            internal inconsistency. Even though ScionBrowser was
            implemented in way not to allow these inconsistencies, it
            can not be excluded that it could happen. If it does please 
            notify the @{"author" LINK "Problem"} about this message and 
            provide as many details as possible under what condition this 
            message appeared.

Each of these categories might be followed by exactly one of the
following messages:

      OK
      
            Should appear only in the developers version as a DEBUG
            message.
            
      One of the required libraries is missing.
      
            ScionBrowser was not able to open one of the required 
            libraries. Either the library was not in the LIBS:
            directory or not in the required version.
            
      The Scion Genealogist screen could not be locked.
      
            ScionBrowser was unable to lock the screen from Scion
            Genealogist or the default public screen.
            
      The window could not be created.
      
            ScionBrowser was unable to create a window. Most likely
            due to memory constraints. Make sure you have enough free
            memory.
            
      The person to be displayed is NULL.
      
            This is an INTERNAL message.
            
      An unknown IDCMP flag was returned by Intuition.
      
            This is an INTERNAL message.
            
      INTERNAL Unknown ErrorCode <number>
      
            This is an INTERNAL message.

@ENDNODE

##------------------------------------------------------------------------
##  Limitations         
##------------------------------------------------------------------------

@NODE Limitations "Limitations"
                             Limitations     

Here is a list of known limitations of ScionBrowser:

       *  Displays only one marriage per person properly, any
          additional wife is not properly conected
       *  No window sliders to scroll display
       *  There is a problem when you try to display a tree
          for a context person which has more than 12 generations
          of ancestors (this is going back ~240 years)! Initially only 
          weird lines appear, for higher generations the system might 
          freeze. I am currently tracking down the reason for that, 
          until then BE AWARE. And hey, this is only version 1.0.
          
I am convinced that all of these limitations will be solved with the
release of the next version (in early 1998).
          

@ENDNODE

